	   <tr><td colspan=2>Also comming from a VT enabled guild doing third tier pop mobs I can tell you our hybrids would probably not ask for this.<br><br>While all of your arguments are correct in principle, something many people forget is that it takes a LOT of loot to equip any average size raiding guild.&nbsp;&nbsp;We raid with between 40 and 60 people.  That means we have a member base of about 80-100.  VT only gives you around 30 loots per clearing, and can only be done once every 2-3 weeks depending on your rotation.  That means you cannot depend soley on VT loot to raise ALL of your casters to FT15.<br><br>Given the choice of a caster at FT15 and a hybrid at FT15 - the casters will always go first.<br><br>I wont argue that it is a nice item for Hybrids.  But saying that &quot;this should go to this class because&quot; always ignores the fact that each guild is in its own unique position and must distribute loot accordingly.  On servers with 8 guilds in VT - I doubt this item would ever go to a hybrid.  On servers with 2 or 3, it might happen more often.  My bet would be that this almost always goes to pure casters.<br><br>Xalion Buscador<br>65 Arch Lich<br>Odysseys - Xev<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
